25/04/2011
ATHENS, Greece -- Prime Minister George Papandreou spoke by phone Saturday (April 23rd) with Libyan counterpart Ali al-Baghdadi al-Mahmudi about potential Greek mediation to end NATO bombings in Libya, ANA news agency reported. 
Papandreou urged al-Mahmudi to end the violence against opponents of Libyan leader Muammar Gaddafi. 
On Friday, Papandreou talked by phone with Russian President Dmitry Medvedev. 
They reiterated their countries' willingness to "provide any necessary mediation help in order to resolve the conflict in Libya peacefully" and agreed that "the assistance of the international community can only be provided in the framework of the mandate granted by the UN Security Council resolution." (ANA-MPA - 23/04/11; Xinhua, ANA-MPA - 22/04/11)
